1º Install Ubuntu Release 12.04 (precise) 64 bit
2º Install the script with the important apps
	- sudo sh installFirst.sh 
3º Conky configuration
	- mv conkyrc /home/username/.conkyrc
	- go to System tools-->Preferences-->Startup applications
	- insert conky
4º CompizConfig Settings Manager
	-check the following app in the Windows Management part:
		- Move Window
		- Put
		- Shift Switcher
		- Static Application Switcher
		- Grid
		- Resize Window
		- Scale 
		- Snapping Windows	
		- Windows Rules
	-Scale configuration
		- Go to Behaviour tab
		- Go to Multi Output Mode and select "On current output device"
5º Theme configuration
	- Go to System Settings-->Ubuntu Tweak-->Overview
	- Select theme
	- Add the following configuration:
		- Gtk theme: Ambiance
		- Icon theme: default
		- Cursor theme: handhelds
		- Windows theme: delorean-light-theme-3.6
		
